<FIRST>r a PM-WeatherpageWeather     10-14 0437</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Weatherpage Weather,0448</SECOND>
<HEAD>Tropical Storm Jerry Nears Coast; Record Highs Across Nation</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Much of the nation enjoyed unseasonably warm temperatures early
today, while the Gulf Coast region braced for the approach of
Tropical Storm Jerry.
   A hurricane watch was in effect from Texas to the Mississippi
River early today as Jerry appeared set to reach hurricane strength
in the Gulf of Mexico, which was already facing abnormally high
tides.
   Jerry developed rapidly from a tropical depression off the
Mexican coast and late Friday had maximum sustained winds of 70 mph.
   Rain dampened Atlanta early today, but most of the rest of the
nation enjoyed fair weather. Temperatures were in the 60s
throughout much of the East and Midwest.
   On Friday, communities from Baltimore to Cheyenne, Wyo., broke
or tied their record high temperatures for the date. In Cheyenne,
the temperature reached 80 degrees for the first time in 110 years
on that date, while Baltimore tied a 1954 mark when the temperature
reached 88 degrees.
   Lack of rain during the past several weeks along with the
unseasonably hot temperatures brought the fire danger in Colorado
to the extreme category.
   The high temperature for the nation Friday was 103 degrees at
Borrego Springs, Calif.
   Other reports at 3 a.m. EDT:
   _East: Albany, N.Y. 42 fair; Atlanta 67 rain; Boston 57 fair;
Charleston, S.C. 67 cloudy; Chattanooga 64 foggy; Cincinnati 60
fair; Cleveland 60 partly cloudy; Detroit 54 partly cloudy;
Hatteras 60 foggy; Jacksonville 65 partly cloudy; Key West 83 fair;
Knoxville 61 hazy; Macon 65 foggy; Miami 78 partly cloudy; New York
58 fair; Philadelphia 57 partly cloudy; Pittsburgh 57 partly
cloudy; Portland, Maine 42 fair; Richmond 60 foggy; Tampa 75 fair;
Washington, D.C. 64 foggy.
   _Central: Birmingham 61 foggy; Denver 54 cloudy; Des Moines 65
partly cloudy; Indianapolis 61 fair; Kansas City 68 fair; Little
Rock 63 fair; Louisville 66 fair; Memphis 65 fair; Nashville 60
foggy; Oklahoma City 61 fair; Omaha 57 fair; Rapid City 51 partly
cloudy; St. Louis 70 fair; Minneapolis-St. Paul 49 fair; Sault Ste.
Marie 41 cloudy; San Antonio 67 fair.
   _West: Albuquerque 61 cloudy; Anchorage 34 cloudy; Boise 52
fair; Great Falls 42 partly cloudy; Honolulu 77 partly cloudy; Las
Vegas 71 partly cloudy; Los Angeles 63 foggy; Medford 50 cloudy;
Pendleton 55 cloudy; Phoenix 82 partly cloudy; Portland, Ore. 48
partly cloudy; Reno 48 fair; Salt Lake City 54 cloudy; San Diego 65
cloudy; San Francisco 56 cloudy; Seattle 51 cloudy; Spokane 48
cloudy.
   _International: Calgary 36 windy; Montreal 41 fair; Ottawa 45
fair; Regina 34 partly cloudy; Toronto 50 partly cloudy; Winnipeg
28 fair.
</TEXT>
