<FIRST>u a PM-ColombianExtradition     10-14 0171</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Colombian Extradition,0174</SECOND>
<HEAD>Second Colombian Extradited to U.S.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MIAMI (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The second Colombian to be extradited to the United
States since the nation declared war on drug traffickers arrived in
Miami today to face a federal drug conspiracy indictment, federal
authorities said.
   Ana Rodriguez de Tamayo, 37, was flown into Miami aboard a U.S.
government aircraft and transferred to a federal women's detention
center in suburban Miami for a court appearance by Monday.
   Colombia has been rocked by bombings blamed for at least 10
deaths and more than 140 injuries since President Virgilio Barco
announced an anti-drug push Aug. 19 and drug barons responded by
declaring a war of their own.
   Drug traffickers have been blamed in the recent shooting deaths
of two employees of the anti-drug crusading Colombian newspaper El
Espectador.
   Rodriguez, who was arrested last month, is not on a U.S. list of
the 12 most wanted Colombian traffickers. Neither was Eduardo
Martinez Romero, who was sent to Atlanta Sept. 6 to face federal
money laudering charges.
</TEXT>
