<HEAD>Toothpaste Changes Name Seen As Offensive</HEAD>
<DATELINE>KUALA LUMPUR, Malaysia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Distributors of a toothpaste
called ``Darkie'' said Saturday they are changing the name to
``Darlie'' because the former name was considered racially
offensive.
   Hawley and Hazel Ltd., which has been distributing the
toothpaste here for more than 40 years, said in a statement it
would spend about $370,000 to promote the name change.
   The company said it has about a 30 percent share of the
toothpaste market in Malaysia and that the name change followed
complaints of racial insensitivity.
