<FIRST>r i AM-Communists-Quotes     10-14 0241</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Communists-Quotes,0246</SECOND>
<HEAD>Quotes from European Communists</HEAD>
<UNK>With AM-Europe-Communists, Bjt</UNK>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Here is what officials of various Communist
parties have been saying about events in the East bloc:
   ``Centrally organized socialism with a one-party system is
bankrupt _ that much is clear from events in Eastern Europe.'' _
Dutch Communist Party leader Ina Brouwer.
   ``How would you feel if the government in France considered that
the citizens of Britain were actually the citizens of France and
could be given French passports just for the asking?'' _ Tony
Chater, editor of The Morning Star, Britain's Communist daily, on
West Germany's assistance to East German refugees.
   ``I did not think nationalisms could become such a problem. It
could become a catastrophe.'' _ Jacques Moins, Belgian Communist
Party member, on nationalist ferment in the Soviet Union.
   ``We obviously aren't overly impressed by what's happened in
Poland and Hungary. Whatever difficulty any party faces in
mobilizing support, it is not going to be solved by disbanding and
abandoning one's aims.'' _ Eoin O Murchu, deputy chairman,
Communist Party of Ireland.
   ``They were too quick with the police nightsticks.'' _ Kaare
Andre Nilsen, leader of the Norwegian Communist Party, on East
German police handling of demonstrators.
   ``In every Western country the whole point is that parties try
to become the government. Here we praise ourselves for getting the
party out of government.'' _ Soviet Communist Party intellectual,
quoted by the Guardian newspaper in London.
</TEXT>
