<HEAD>Food Poisoning Kills Centenarian and Injures 150</HEAD>
<DATELINE>KARACHI, Pakistan (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Tainted sweets killed a centenarian
Saturday and injured another 150 people in the southern port city
of Karachi, police said.
   No one claimed responsibility and police suspect the sweets,
golf-ball size pieces of fried dough, were accidently spoiled.
   Most of the food poisoning victims were treated at local
