<SECOND>AM-Explosives Found,0108</SECOND>
<HEAD>Explosives Found in Shipment of Canned Food</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LIMASSOL, Cyprus (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Explosives and grenades have been
discovered in a shipment of canned food from Lebanon, police
reported Saturday.
   Police spokesman Stelios Neophytou said a search of the shipment
destined for Liberia via the port of Limassol in Cyprus uncovered
TNT, plastic explosives and two hand grenades.
   He said the crates were searched Friday after police were tipped
that they may contain drugs.
   The consignment arrived from the Lebanese port of Sidon on Sept.
29 aboard the Honduras-flag ship Libra, for shipment to Monrovia,
Liberia.
   Customs documents named a Lebanese as the sender.
