<SECOND>AM-Italy-Race Deaths,0133</SECOND>
<HEAD>Race Car Goes Off The Road, Kills Three Onlookers</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PADUA, Italy (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A race car sped off the road and into a
group of spectators Saturday, killing three people and injuring at
least seven, police said.
   The driver and the navigator were not injured when the
Peugeot-205 racer left the road during a minor auto rally near this
northern Italian city and sped into the crowd.
   The Italian news agency ANSA reported that two of the injured
were in critical condition.
   The accident occurred during a special trial of the so-called
``Rally of the Saint'' outside the town of Treporti di Teolo, in
the Padua province.
   Padua is called the city of the saint because it is the site of
the shrine of St. Anthony.
