<FIRST>r a AM-Bound-Gagged     10-14 0200</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Bound-Gagged,0207</SECOND>
<HEAD>Elderly Woman Survives 5{-day Ordeal</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PITTSBURGH (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A 91-year-old woman was hospitalized in stable
condition Saturday after spending 5{ days bound and gagged in her
home without food or water.
   Police found Bessie Johnson on Friday afternoon lying under her
kitchen table, where a thief apparently left her Oct. 7.
   ``They choked her on the bed, wrapped plastic around her neck,''
said police Lt. Edward Kelly. ``She was gagged in the mouth, with a
stocking around her legs, pantyhose around her wrists.''
   The robber stole $17 and a television set, Kelly said.
   Mrs. Johnson, who lives alone in the city's Homewood section,
was taken to St. Francis Health Center suffering dehydration and
bruises.
   The attack left her wrists bruised and blistered, neighbor Relma
Brown said after visting her in the hospital Friday night.
   ``I'm very angry at the person who did this, but she said, `I
kicked him, I kicked him good.''' Mrs. Brown said. ``She is
extremely independent. ... She's in excellent shape for her age.''
   Police and paramedics were called after another neighbor heard
Mrs. Johnson shouting. Mrs. Johnson told police she yelled for help
on several occasions, but was not heard until Friday.
