<HEAD>New Episcopal Bishop of New York Installed</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Bishop Richard Frank Grein was installed
Saturday as the head of the Episcopal Church's Diocese of New York
during ceremonies at the Cathedral of St. John the Divine.
   Grein, formerly the Bishop of Kansas, succeeded the Rt. Rev.
Paul Moore and becomes the 14th Episcopal Bishop of New York.
   The diocese includes the boroughs of Manhattan, Staten Island
and the Bronx, as well as Westchester, Rockland, Dutchess, Putnam,
Ulster, Orange and Sullivan counties.
   Moore was Bishop of New York for 20 years.
