<HEAD>Oklahoma Army National Guardsman Killed While Rappelling From Helicopter</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TOPEKA, Kan. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An Oklahoma Army National Guard instructor
died Saturday after he fell while rappelling from a helicopter in a
demonstration of air assault techniques, a National Guard official
said.
   The soldier fell from his rappelling rope at Forbes Field
airport around 1:30 p.m., and died about two hours later at a
